Issues in surgical treatment of thoraco-lumbar injuries associated with spinal cord injuries in children and adolescents. To evaluate standards of care in surgical treatment of thoracolumbar injuries (TLIs), we reviewed the cases of 79 surgically treated patients (39 males, 36 females) with TLIs and spinal cord injuries occurring from January 1985 to January 2000. We assessed radiographs of fracture-dislocation reductions restorations of sagittal and coronal alignment of injured segments